We are of the opinion that in the original referendum we were not given adequate information as to the consequences of remaining or leaving;
that the leave and remain campaigners relied on information that was incomplete and inaccurate (for true contribution details see HM Treasury, European Finances 2016);
that we were never made aware of the complications of leaving especially the Irish border issue, domicile issues for both British and European expatriates, the risk of non-tariff barriers, the cost of funding commitments entered into prior to leaving (the so-called exit fee).
